cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the generalization of neural networks. It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it focuses on the behavior of neural networks. Additionally, since the paper discusses the performance of ReLU neural networks, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, since the paper introduces statistical measures to analyze network derivatives, it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
